## Runbook 2: Stuck Open Position (Cannot Close)

**Symptoms**: Exit order submitted but not filling, position open past expected hold time, orphan or rejection messages in logs, `/api/status.live.has_position == true` long after the contract should have exited

### Diagnose
```bash
# Read current live position state and any orphans
curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $DASHBOARD_API_TOKEN" http://localhost:8000/api/status \
  | jq '{live, orphaned_positions, live_decision}'

# Check the last 200 lines for fill or rejection events
docker logs kbtc-bot --tail=200 2>&1 | rg -i 'orphan|reject|fill_stream|emergency|exit_failed'
```

### Act
```bash
# Step A — close everything Kalshi reports we hold (reads exchange state, not local cache)
# This pauses trading, calls KalshiOrderClient.close_all_exchange_positions(), then re-syncs the wallet.
curl -X POST -H "Authorization: Bearer $DASHBOARD_API_TOKEN" \
  http://localhost:8000/api/close-all-exchange-positions

# Step B — if Step A fails or partially succeeds, escalate to the kill switch
# (force-closes via PositionManager; converts unfillable positions to orphans)
curl -X POST -H "Authorization: Bearer $DASHBOARD_API_TOKEN" \
  http://localhost:8000/api/emergency-stop

# Step C — if contract has < 5 min to expiry, do nothing further
# Kalshi will settle the contract and the wallet will resolve automatically.
# Run sync_live_bankroll on next bot restart to reconcile recorded vs wallet PnL.
```

If both endpoints fail (e.g. `INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS`, `MARKET_CLOSED`, persistent `RATE_LIMITED`), grep the live logs for the underlying API error and decide whether to wait for settlement or open a Kalshi support ticket.

### Record
See **Recording the Incident** above. SEV-1 → Discord post required.

