## Post-Incident Template
```markdown
## Incident Report — [Date]

**Severity**: SEV-[1/2/3/4]
**Duration**: [start] → [resolved] (X minutes)
**Detected By**: [Discord alert / dashboard / user report]

**What Happened**:
[Plain English description]

**Impact**:
- Open positions affected: [Y/N]
- Estimated P&L impact: $X
- Trading halted for: N minutes

**Root Cause**:
[Technical root cause]

**Resolution**:
[Steps taken to resolve]

**Prevention**:
[ ] Action item 1 — assigned to [role]
[ ] Action item 2 — assigned to [role]
```

## Guardrails
- Never restart a crashing bot more than 3 times in 30 minutes without investigating root cause first
- Never reset the drawdown peak (`/api/reset-drawdown`) without logging the reason and approver in `incidents.log`
- Always check `/api/status.live` for an open position before taking any remediation action — position safety first
- Every SEV-1 and SEV-2 requires a Discord post in `#kbtc-errors` and a line in `/home/botuser/kbtc/logs/incidents.log`, no exceptions
- Incident logs (`errored_trades`, `incidents.log`, Discord history) are compliance records — never delete them
- If you find a command in this runbook that no longer matches the codebase, fix it here in the same change — outdated runbooks are worse than no runbook
